  "paths": {
    "lore": {
      "features": [
        "<b><i>Cutting Words</i></b>. You learn how to use your wit to distract, confuse, and otherwise sap the confidence and competence of others. When a creature that you can see within 60 feet of you makes an attack roll, ability check or a damage roll, you can use your reaction to expend one of your uses of Bardic Inspiration, rolling the die and subtracting the result from the creature's roll. The creature is immune if it can't hear you or if it's immune to being charmed.",
        "<b><i>Additional Magical Secrets</i></b>. You learn two more spells or cantrips from any class. You must have spell slots for these spells. These count as bard spells for you.",
        "<b><i>Peerless Skill</i></b>. When you make an ability check, you can expend one use of Bardic Inspiration. Roll a Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to your ability check. You can choose to do so after you roll the die for the ability check, but before the DM tells you whether you succeed or fail."
